00:17:06.260 --> 00:17:10.500
I didn't demo that, because that's not a very interesting demo, but it's a big deal if you're

00:17:10.500 --> 00:17:15.300
the type of person who wants to kick off a job, go have coffee or go to bed and then

00:17:15.300 --> 00:17:20.739
come back the next day and reconnect and see the results of that job, right?

00:17:20.739 --> 00:17:23.380
This is something that VS Code doesn't have.

00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:27.939
I think a lot of people have been asking for it, but Positron, it's implemented in remote

00:17:27.939 --> 00:17:29.939
SSH, which is cool.

